'''Stormtrooper droids''' were [[Droid/Legends|droids]] designed to look like [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]]. [[IG-88B/Legends|IG-88B]] had 100 of these droids produced on [[Mechis III/Legends|Mechis III]]. They were used to [[Battle en route to the second Death Star|attack]] and destroy an Imperial [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] carrying a [[Computer core/Legends|computer core]] destined for the [[Death Star II/Legends|Death Star II]], and then escorted a decoy core containing [[IG-88A/Legends|IG-88A's]] consciousness to the Death Star, where they were put on construction duty by an unsuspecting [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Tiaan Jerjerrod/Legends|Jerjerrod]]. The droids were designed to [[Self-destruct mechanism/Legends|self-destruct]] if their true nature was discovered; when a crane accident damaged one of the droids, the resulting explosion wiped out the entire work crew.<ref name="Tale of IG-88">{{StoryCite|story=Therefore I Am: The Tale of IG-88|book=Tales of the Bounty Hunters}}</ref>

